  "texts": [
    "This is quite straightforward to do, using the usual machinery of modern cosmology, which is covered in many textbooks, and need not be repeated here.",
    "Let us nonetheless draw attention to the main concept relevant to lensing, namely the different ways of expressing distance.",
    "The observable associated with distance is the redshift z.",
    "While an observed z may contain a small kinematic contribution (of order 10 -3), cosmological redshifts are essentially wavelengths expanding with the universe.",
    "Thus a redshift of z refers to an epoch when the scale factor of the universe was 1 + z smaller than now."
  ],
